Hash: SHA512

annotations:
  artifacthub.io/changes: |
    - kind: changed
      description: "Varnish is now a sharded StatefulSet (ADR 0018): the edge discovers Varnish shards via a headless Service's SRV records and routes every permutation of an image to the same shard using rendezvous (HRW) hashing, so each image is cached on exactly one shard — no cross-replica duplication, ~Nx effective cache and hit ratio. Replaces the single-replica Varnish Deployment; varnish.replicaCount now defaults to 3. Do NOT put varnish.replicaCount behind an HPA (changing it reshards ~1/N of the cache). Requires a sharding-capable edge image."
    - kind: added
      description: "Varnish headless Service (<release>-varnish-headless; clusterIP: None, publishNotReadyAddresses: true) governs the StatefulSet and provides stable per-pod SRV/A records for shard discovery. The edge is wired to it via EDGE_VARNISH_HEADLESS; the plain ClusterIP Service is kept for debug/health only."
    - kind: added
      description: "varnish PodDisruptionBudget is enabled by default (maxUnavailable: 1) so shard rolls/drains cycle one shard at a time."
    - kind: fixed
      description: "varnish.pdb.minAvailable was silently ignored (the template always keyed on the default maxUnavailable); it now takes precedence when set, matching the OSC PDB."
    - kind: added
      description: "Per-component topologySpreadConstraints override (edge/varnish/backend/fetcher/processor/objectStorageCache); previously hardcoded and non-overridable. Set e.g. varnish.topologySpreadConstraints with whenUnsatisfiable: DoNotSchedule to force each cache shard onto a distinct node."
    - kind: changed
      description: "Consistent values interface for deployment identity: all identity labels now use friendly camelCase keys under `identity:` (environment, region, availabilityZone, deploy, product, hostId, provider, hostname, hostType, hostImage) which the chart maps to the underlying env vars — replacing the raw UPPERCASE env-var pass-through. The deployment environment moved from `imageengine.environment` to `identity.environment` (still the single source of truth for logs/Sentry/OTel). `provider` stays top-level (infra presets + default provider label). BREAKING for anyone who set `identity.*` or `imageengine.environment` — pre-release, no compatibility shim; update your -f overrides."
  artifacthub.io/signKey: |
    fingerprint: C3A55111ED91FEDE4A82A4B4463266060957C4B3
